commands.description:
Extract all value for a designated field in a Json structure. 
[
  {
    "Id": "1234",
    "Status": "Closed",
    "ClosedDate": "2024-03-25"
  },
  {
    "Id": "5678",
    "Status": "Closed",
    "ClosedDate": "2024-03-25"
  }
]

Copy in your clipboard :
1234
5678

Modify Json structure from your cliboard.
You can replace all values for an attribute in one time, and keep only and keep only those you need.
Ex :
[
  {
    "Id": "1234",
    "Name": "Case 00001",
    "Status": "Open",
    "ClosedDate": ""
  },
  {
    "Id": "5678",
    "Name": "Case 00002",
    "Status": "Open",
    "ClosedDate": ""
  }
]

To : 
[
  {
    "Id": "1234",
    "Status": "Closed",
    "ClosedDate": "2024-03-25"
  },
  {
    "Id": "5678",
    "Status": "Closed",
    "ClosedDate": "2024-03-25"
  }
]
